HEADWORD: Melanosis
<hw>Mel`a*no"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ a growing
black, fr. <grk>me`las</grk>, <grk>me`lanos</grk>, black.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The morbid deposition of black matter, often of a
malignant character, causing pigmented tumors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

